trans-unit.source: A PersonalizationDictionary instance is a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry> objects, which consist of a personalization scope and an object value.

trans-unit.source: These entries are assigned a key in the PersonalizationDictionary object.
trans-unit.target: Disse postene er tilordnet en nøkkel i PersonalizationDictionary-objektet.

trans-unit.source: A good practice is to add all properties to the dictionary using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> method, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: Er lurt å legge til alle egenskapene i ordlisten ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>metoden, uavhengig av siden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework saves the information in the appropriate way; for example, shared data is saved when the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: .NET Framework lagrer informasjonen på riktig måte; for eksempel delt lagres når siden er i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: However, shared properties are not saved when a Web Parts value is being saved, the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added with the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: Men delte egenskaper er ikke lagret når webdeler verdien lagres, siden er i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang, og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll ble lagt til med siden i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: When a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, you can add name and state information that is associated with either <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.

trans-unit.source: In <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, you can add name and state information associated only with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: I <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang, kan du legge til navnet og tilstand informasjon knyttet til bare <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: It is a good practice, however, to add all properties to the dictionary using <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> including properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: Det er lurt, å legge til alle egenskapene i ordlisten ved hjelp av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>inkludert egenskaper med <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>eller <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang, uavhengig av siden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework only saves the properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope when appropriate.
trans-unit.target: .NET Framework lagrer bare egenskaper med <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang når det er nødvendig.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: In other words, shared properties are not saved when a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control that was initially added in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: Delt med andre ord, egenskaper er ikke lagret når en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll som opprinnelig ble lagt til i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfanget lagres senere mens siden er i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: In an opposite scenario, if a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added to the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, and the control is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, custom shared property values are saved (along with custom user-scoped properties).
trans-unit.target: I det motsatte scenariet Hvis en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll ble lagt til siden i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfang og kontrollen lagres senere mens siden er i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfanget egendefinerte delte egenskapsverdier lagres (sammen med egendefinerte område bruker egenskaper).</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: For details on personalization data and how shared and user-scoped properties are affected by the personalization scope of the page, see the [Web Parts Personalization Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) topic.
trans-unit.target: For informasjon om personlige data og hvordan delte og bruker-område er berørt av område på siden, kan du se den [oversikt over webdeler personlige data](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) emnet.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Add%2A> method checks several details to ensure the validity of `value` and `key` before attempting to add them to the personalization dictionary.
